Echoes Fade is the band formerly known as Doug Douglas. They are quite active and are looking to play shows, so if you want a band to play, give Users/domenicsantangelo domenic a call.

Awards and Recognitions
    They won the Picnic Day 2004 Davis Rock Challenge, which resulted in being granted the title the Best Band in Davis and some other cool stuff which is outlined in more detail at the Doug Douglas page.
    Their single http://www.garageband.com/song?|pe1|S8LTM0LdsaSkZlGxZ2k Falter was named Track of the Day for April 29, 2005 at http://www.garageband.com/echoesfade GarageBand.com
    Their single http://www.garageband.com/song?|pe1|S8LTM0LdsaSkZlG_a20 Rhetoric was named Track of the Day for May 11, 2005 at http://www.garageband.com/echoesfade GarageBand.com
    Their single I Will Give was named Track of the Day for May 18, 2005 at http://www.garageband.com/echoesfade GarageBand.com
     http://www.garageband.com/song?|pe1|S8LTM0LdsaSkZlG_amo I Will Give was named Emo Track of the Week, the week of 18 July, 2005 at http://www.garageband.com/echoesfade GarageBand.com
     http://www.garageband.com/song?|pe1|S8LTM0LdsaSkZlG_amo I Will Give won many other awards, including Best Male Vocals, Best Guitars, Best Lyrics, Best Melody, etc., and reached an alltime high of #1 in the http://www.garageband.com/genre/emo/current.html?|pe1|S9ncJmn4vPTJFy3dTE8WsFiblySIA Emo genre.

